WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:15.000
Downloaded From AnimeArcadia.lk

00:06.938 --> 00:08.938
[foreboding music playing]

00:13.521 --> 00:14.521
My God.

00:15.438 --> 00:17.480
It's worse than I imagined.

00:18.271 --> 00:20.730
An entire horde of--

00:20.813 --> 00:22.313
Monsters.

00:22.396 --> 00:26.605
How much longer we gotta sit on our dicks
before you tell us what this is about?

00:26.688 --> 00:29.105
Your employer will be here shortly.

00:29.188 --> 00:30.896
He'll fill you in on the target.

00:30.980 --> 00:32.063
[mercenary] "Target"?

00:32.646 --> 00:34.188
As in just one?

00:34.688 --> 00:36.771
Hell of a lot of guns for one guy.

00:37.355 --> 00:41.355
Yeah, with odds like these,
you might actually win a fight. [chuckles]

00:42.938 --> 00:43.771
Okay.

00:46.521 --> 00:49.188
And this is the species
we're trying to save?

00:49.271 --> 00:51.271
I still say we just go in ourselves.

00:51.355 --> 00:56.146
Heh. We're a tactical strike force
trained for precision demon removal.

00:56.230 --> 00:59.480
This mission requires blunt instruments.

01:00.313 --> 01:02.105
[agent] They certainly qualify.

01:02.188 --> 01:05.021
Let them fight over
who's the baddest dude in the room.

01:05.563 --> 01:06.938
We know who it really is.

01:07.021 --> 01:08.021
[door opens]

01:14.105 --> 01:15.563
Oh my God.

01:16.063 --> 01:17.146
Is that…

01:17.230 --> 01:18.855
The vice fucking president.

01:19.855 --> 01:22.396
Since there's no need for introductions,
I'll get right to it.

01:23.063 --> 01:25.813
This, gentlemen,
is your primary objective.

01:26.313 --> 01:30.063
An item of critical importance
to our national security.

01:30.146 --> 01:34.438
However, seeing as this item
officially does not exist,

01:34.938 --> 01:36.980
we need it retrieved off the books.

01:37.480 --> 01:41.646
We've tracked the amulet to this location.

01:41.730 --> 01:44.438
You'll find it around the neck
of its current owner,

01:44.521 --> 01:47.938
a man the US government
considers a top-level threat.

01:48.021 --> 01:52.355
He is extremely volatile,
and prodigiously gifted in combat.

01:53.021 --> 01:57.188
Engage him only with
the full brunt of your firepower.

01:58.230 --> 02:00.980
This superman son of a bitch got a name?

02:01.063 --> 02:04.021
His name is Dante.

02:07.230 --> 02:09.438
[laughing]

02:09.521 --> 02:11.313
[mercenaries laughing]

02:11.396 --> 02:14.105
That's the guy
we're supposed to be worried about?

02:14.188 --> 02:16.855
What's he going to do? Get hair dye on us?

02:27.730 --> 02:30.021
["Rollin' (Air Raid Vehicle)"
by Limp Bizkit playing]

02:30.105 --> 02:31.896
♪ Throw your hands up ♪

02:31.980 --> 02:34.438
♪ Your… your… your hands up ♪

02:34.521 --> 02:37.188
♪ Throw your hands up
Throw your hands up ♪

02:37.271 --> 02:39.938
♪ Move in, now move out
Hands up, now hands down ♪

02:40.021 --> 02:42.355
♪ Back up, back up
Tell me what you're gonna do now ♪

02:42.438 --> 02:45.063
♪ Breathe in, now breathe out
Hands up, now hands down ♪

02:45.146 --> 02:47.230
♪ Back up, back up
Tell me what you're gonna do now ♪

02:47.313 --> 02:50.021
♪ Keep rollin', rollin'
Rollin', rollin' ♪

02:50.105 --> 02:52.438
♪ Keep rollin', rollin'
Rollin', rollin' ♪

02:52.521 --> 02:54.855
♪ Keep rollin', rollin'
Rollin', rollin' ♪

02:54.938 --> 02:57.438
♪ Keep rollin', rollin'
Rollin', rollin' ♪

02:57.521 --> 02:59.646
♪ Hey, ladies, hey, fellas ♪

02:59.730 --> 03:02.521
♪ And the people that don't give a **** ♪

03:02.605 --> 03:04.688
♪ All the lovers, all the haters ♪

03:04.771 --> 03:07.521
♪ And all the people
That call themselves players ♪

03:07.605 --> 03:09.605
♪ Hot mommas, pimp daddies ♪

03:09.688 --> 03:12.188
♪ And the people rollin' up in Caddies ♪

03:12.271 --> 03:15.146
♪ Hey, rockers, hip-hoppers ♪

03:15.230 --> 03:17.355
♪ And everybody all around the world ♪

03:17.438 --> 03:20.105
♪ Move in, now move out
Hands up, now hands down ♪

03:20.188 --> 03:22.605
♪ Back up, back up
Tell me what you're gonna do now ♪

03:22.688 --> 03:24.813
♪ Breathe in, now breathe out
Hands up, now hands down ♪

03:24.896 --> 03:27.480
♪ Back up, back up
Tell me what you're gonna do now ♪

03:27.563 --> 03:29.688
♪ Keep rollin'
Rollin', rollin', rollin' ♪

03:29.771 --> 03:32.480
♪ Keep rollin'
Rollin', rollin', rollin' ♪

03:32.563 --> 03:35.188
♪ Keep rollin'
Rollin', rollin', rollin' ♪

03:35.271 --> 03:36.271
[song trails off]

03:44.063 --> 03:45.563
[mercenaries laughing]

03:47.230 --> 03:49.313
[mercenary] Laugh while you can.

03:50.063 --> 03:51.938
You won't be much longer.

03:52.438 --> 03:55.480
I met Dante once.
Worked with him on a protection job.

03:56.355 --> 03:59.521
I've dealt with killers and roughnecks
of every grade,

03:59.605 --> 04:02.063
but this guy, he's something else.

04:02.146 --> 04:04.855
The way he moved, the hits he took.

04:05.896 --> 04:08.021
I'd be dead now if it wasn't for him.

04:08.105 --> 04:11.563
And you'll all be dead soon enough
if you go after him.

04:13.188 --> 04:16.646
[grunts] Ain't no amount of money
you could offer that'd be worth--

04:16.730 --> 04:19.396
[Baines] Five hundred thousand.

04:19.896 --> 04:24.771
The bounty is 500,000 for whoever
brings in Dante with the amulet.

04:25.396 --> 04:27.896
And a bonus if he's alive for questioning.

04:30.021 --> 04:31.438
Well, all right.

04:32.146 --> 04:33.605
Let's go get him, then.

04:33.688 --> 04:36.438
We will be deploying a civilian asset

04:36.521 --> 04:38.896
to keep Dante distracted as you move in.

04:38.980 --> 04:41.063
So, if we're doing all the work,

04:41.146 --> 04:43.813
why'd you bring the Boy Scout patrol here?

04:43.896 --> 04:46.396
They don't look like no jarheads to me.

04:49.230 --> 04:52.855
These soldiers will be in the field
overseeing the operation.

04:52.938 --> 04:54.980
You'll deliver the package to them.

04:55.521 --> 04:57.563
The contract opens as of midnight tonight.

04:58.771 --> 04:59.771
That's all.

05:07.105 --> 05:10.230
You in the cap with the nice eyes.
Hold on a second.

05:10.896 --> 05:12.646
[chuckles]

05:12.730 --> 05:15.188
You see something you like, sweetheart?

05:16.230 --> 05:17.813
[agent] What you said was correct.

05:19.105 --> 05:20.480
We're not jarheads.

05:21.355 --> 05:23.021
We're demon hunters.

05:23.105 --> 05:24.730
You're joking.

05:25.438 --> 05:26.313
I know.

05:26.396 --> 05:27.938
It's a lot to take in.

05:28.021 --> 05:29.771
Someone walks up and tells you,

05:29.855 --> 05:32.230
"Demons are real,
and it's my job to kill them."

05:33.063 --> 05:35.396
You're thinking the same thing
anyone else would.

05:35.480 --> 05:38.230
But unfortunately, it's the truth.

05:38.313 --> 05:41.063
The worst truth is that
not only are demons real,

05:41.646 --> 05:44.230
they're really fucking hard to kill.

05:44.313 --> 05:46.563
We've had to come up with our own methods.

05:47.063 --> 05:48.105
Like these.

05:48.188 --> 05:49.480
Anti-demon bullets.

05:50.605 --> 05:53.688
Hit a human with one,
and it works like any other bullet.

05:53.771 --> 05:55.396
But hit a demon,

05:55.480 --> 05:56.980
and this little liquid explodes

05:57.063 --> 05:59.896
the instant it comes
in contact with their DNA.

06:00.396 --> 06:02.105
That's, uh, good to know.

06:02.855 --> 06:04.980
Sometimes they pass for human.

06:05.563 --> 06:08.021
They can even be incredibly convincing.

06:08.521 --> 06:09.813
It's in the proportions.

06:10.313 --> 06:13.480
The arms or legs
will be a little too long.

06:13.563 --> 06:15.938
Facial features too far apart.

06:16.021 --> 06:18.563
Like they haven't quite evolved
all the way.

06:18.646 --> 06:21.021
There's also something in the eyes.

06:21.730 --> 06:25.188
A void where the glimmer
of a soul should be.

06:26.646 --> 06:28.688
And, of course, the smell.

06:29.188 --> 06:33.313
A faint mix of sulfur and cow shit.

06:35.438 --> 06:36.813
[frantic industrial music building]

06:36.896 --> 06:38.688
[heart beating rapidly]

06:48.813 --> 06:50.855
[music intensifies]

06:51.896 --> 06:53.021
[sharp humming]

06:55.605 --> 06:57.605
[intense industrial music continuing]

07:07.355 --> 07:08.355
[music subsides]

07:12.771 --> 07:15.146
Devil spawn motherfucker.

07:16.521 --> 07:19.355
You were solid, boss.
I don't think I even saw you blink.

07:19.438 --> 07:21.480
I knew I was in good hands.

07:21.980 --> 07:24.438
Lieutenant Arkham is
the pride of this righteous army.

07:25.021 --> 07:27.188
I'm just helping secure
a world for our species.

07:27.271 --> 07:28.771
That's all that matters.

07:28.855 --> 07:29.813
Indeed.

07:29.896 --> 07:32.188
And our world could not ask
for a better soldier.

07:32.271 --> 07:36.230
[soldier] Was told to report to this room.
At least, I think it was this room.

07:36.313 --> 07:37.146
[Baines] Let him in.

07:37.230 --> 07:39.563
…a lot of nondescript doors
and hallways down here.

07:42.688 --> 07:43.688
[agent] Who the…

07:44.355 --> 07:47.771
This is Anders, your newest member
of DARKCOM Elite Ops.

07:47.855 --> 07:49.646
"Anders"? Aren't you…

07:49.730 --> 07:52.396
The only survivor
of the White Rabbit's ambush.

07:52.480 --> 07:55.980
I've watched your mission tapes.
It is an honor to serve with you, ma'am.

07:56.063 --> 07:57.396
Uh, Lieutenant?

07:58.021 --> 07:59.105
Mary?

07:59.188 --> 08:01.188
Lieutenant. Got you. 10-4.

08:01.271 --> 08:02.605
[chuckles]

08:02.688 --> 08:04.355
Welcome to the team, chief.

08:04.438 --> 08:07.563
-You sure about this guy, sir?
-He requested this assignment.

08:07.646 --> 08:10.355
God has tested him,
and he was found worthy.

08:11.105 --> 08:12.771
Soldier, where is the asset?

08:12.855 --> 08:16.313
While I've got you here,
who do I talk to about the menu, huh?

08:16.396 --> 08:18.605
I can't even get a decent plate of…

08:20.355 --> 08:21.355
Oh. Uh…

08:22.105 --> 08:25.146
So, wait, what do I have to do again?

08:27.396 --> 08:29.396
[tense, mysterious music playing]

08:33.105 --> 08:34.271
[clattering at door]

08:35.355 --> 08:36.355
Dante?

08:38.646 --> 08:39.730
You here?

08:42.563 --> 08:44.271
Hey, Dante!

08:44.355 --> 08:46.605
It's your buddy, Enzo!

08:47.813 --> 08:48.813
[sighs]

08:48.896 --> 08:50.438
-Ah, nobody's-- Whoa!
-[gun cocks]

08:51.896 --> 08:54.355
Dante! You are here.

08:54.438 --> 08:55.688
[haltingly] Thank God!

08:55.771 --> 08:57.938
I… I was worried I missed you.

08:58.021 --> 09:00.396
Hey, Enzo. How've you been?

09:00.480 --> 09:02.271
Ah, I could do better,
to tell you the truth.

09:02.355 --> 09:06.355
Like if you didn't have a… a barrel
pressed to my temple right now.

09:06.438 --> 09:07.980
Wish I could help you out there.

09:08.063 --> 09:10.355
I do have a funny story for you, though.

09:10.438 --> 09:11.855
You're gonna love this.

09:11.938 --> 09:14.605
So, my last job, the one you gave me,

09:15.105 --> 09:18.396
it turned out to be a setup
so a shape-shifting demon baby

09:18.480 --> 09:20.188
could try to steal my necklace.

09:20.271 --> 09:21.938
Crazy, right?

09:22.021 --> 09:23.396
[laughing awkwardly]

09:23.480 --> 09:25.896
That's the craziest thing I ever heard.

09:25.980 --> 09:27.688
[frenetic industrial music building]

09:29.230 --> 09:31.063
[Enzo] It wasn't my fault, Dante.

09:31.146 --> 09:34.313
Honest. Don't blame poor old Enzo.

09:34.396 --> 09:36.938
I'm just a middleman. A nobody.

09:37.021 --> 09:40.146
It was the guy who gave me the job,
the White Rabbit.

09:40.230 --> 09:43.146
He's the one who set the whole thing up.

09:43.646 --> 09:47.063
See, he comes into my office,
talking all smooth,

09:47.146 --> 09:49.771
and I’m mesmerized!

09:53.438 --> 09:55.688
All we've got to do is get to him first,

09:56.271 --> 09:59.355
and then split the 500 between us.

10:00.021 --> 10:02.646
[Dante] You're saying
you only sent me into a trap

10:02.730 --> 10:06.480
because a demon that looks like
a giant rabbit tricked you into doing it?

10:06.563 --> 10:07.855
Pretty much. Yeah.

10:10.646 --> 10:12.105
All right, that checks out.

10:12.188 --> 10:13.563
What are you doing here?

10:13.646 --> 10:16.021
I brought you the second half of your fee.

10:16.105 --> 10:20.355
Just 'cause the job was fake
don't mean you don't get paid, right?

10:21.063 --> 10:24.396
Pure, uncut American green.

10:24.480 --> 10:26.980
And all you had to do
was fight a baby for it.

10:27.063 --> 10:28.563
[Dante] And my own brother.

10:28.646 --> 10:31.771
The shape-shifter showed up again later
disguised as him.

10:31.855 --> 10:35.480
Nothing like how he'd actually look now,
but still, it was a good effort.

10:35.563 --> 10:37.355
Oh. Your brother?

10:37.438 --> 10:39.355
Talk about digging up the past, huh?

10:39.438 --> 10:40.813
Ugh.

10:40.896 --> 10:41.855
You all right, kid?

10:41.938 --> 10:44.605
I keep telling you. What's my only rule?

10:44.688 --> 10:48.230
I'll take any job that pays,
especially if it involves killing demons.

10:48.313 --> 10:51.563
-Just as long as I don't have to care.
-As you don't have to care.

10:51.646 --> 10:55.855
I know. So, you and me,
we're all good now, yeah?

10:55.938 --> 10:58.271
You know, I look at you like my own son.

10:58.355 --> 10:59.855
I would take a bullet for you.

10:59.938 --> 11:01.688
Well, maybe not a bullet.

11:01.771 --> 11:03.980
Definitely a blade, like a little jab.

11:04.063 --> 11:07.730
Point is, I would never
set you up like that on purpose.

11:07.813 --> 11:10.896
So there aren't multiple teams
of mercenaries outside,

11:10.980 --> 11:12.730
closing in around us right now?

11:12.813 --> 11:14.021
Okay. [chuckles]

11:14.105 --> 11:16.938
I set you up this time,
but only 'cause they made me.

11:17.021 --> 11:19.605
I know I've got another one of these…

11:21.188 --> 11:22.355
There it is.

11:22.438 --> 11:26.605
Look, Dante, those guys out there
are after your necklace too,

11:26.688 --> 11:28.480
and it's the feds who are paying them.

11:28.563 --> 11:31.063
This thing goes right to the top.

11:31.146 --> 11:35.896
What say you just give the bling to me,
and I'll take it over to them, huh?

11:35.980 --> 11:37.355
No, muss, no fuss.

11:37.438 --> 11:38.855
I can't do it, Enzo.

11:39.688 --> 11:41.230
She gave me this necklace.

11:42.605 --> 11:47.105
[woman] This isn't just a necklace, Dante.
It's a part of our family's history.

11:47.605 --> 11:50.105
I need you to take good care of it, okay?

11:50.188 --> 11:51.938
You have to keep this safe.

11:52.021 --> 11:52.938
Always.

11:53.438 --> 11:54.355
You promise?

11:55.230 --> 11:59.938
It's the last thing of hers that I have.
No one is going to take it from me.

12:00.021 --> 12:01.021
Fair enough.

12:01.105 --> 12:04.980
I'll just, uh, let you get ready
for the big throwdown then, and head on…

12:05.063 --> 12:07.146
-[gun cocks]
-[Enzo sputtering]

12:07.230 --> 12:09.021
I didn't say we were good yet.

12:10.563 --> 12:12.396
[frenetic music intensifying]

12:27.980 --> 12:30.230
We're here for the amulet.

12:30.313 --> 12:32.105
Drop the gun and hand it over.

12:34.105 --> 12:35.813
I said, drop the gun!

12:36.313 --> 12:37.313
[Enzo struggling]

12:40.063 --> 12:41.771
I don't think that's the guy.

12:41.855 --> 12:43.896
Of course it's not the guy!

13:00.813 --> 13:01.813
[Dante] Heh.

13:03.896 --> 13:05.105
Fire!

13:13.521 --> 13:15.271
Who are we shooting at?

13:15.813 --> 13:16.980
Hey!

13:17.063 --> 13:19.271
[aggressive industrial music playing]

13:42.980 --> 13:44.771
Come on, you ain't shit, pal!

13:50.480 --> 13:51.646
[panicked yelping]

13:53.188 --> 13:55.105
[grunts, groans]

13:57.063 --> 13:58.605
[Enzo struggling]

14:00.438 --> 14:01.605
[Dante] Now we're good.

14:02.355 --> 14:04.355
Was the gag really necessary?

14:05.563 --> 14:07.355
All right, I see your point.

14:08.813 --> 14:12.063
-You managed not to kill any of them.
-I had to add a little challenge.

14:12.146 --> 14:14.396
You wouldn't happen to know
why my family heirloom

14:14.480 --> 14:16.563
is New York's hottest fashion accessory?

14:16.646 --> 14:20.771
If I had that info, I'd have tried
to sell it to you the second I got here.

14:20.855 --> 14:22.146
Give me some credit!

14:22.730 --> 14:23.896
What are you doing now?

14:27.146 --> 14:29.021
I work better with music.

14:29.105 --> 14:31.146
["Guerilla Radio"
by Rage Against the Machine playing]

14:31.230 --> 14:33.230
[rowdy rap metal music playing]

14:37.688 --> 14:39.563
[song continuing in distance]

14:40.563 --> 14:43.063
I'll give you one thing.
This guy's got taste!

15:02.938 --> 15:05.396
♪ Transmission
Third World War, third round ♪

15:05.480 --> 15:06.855
♪ Decade of the weapon of sound… ♪

15:06.938 --> 15:07.771
Go.

15:07.855 --> 15:10.021
♪ No shelter if you're looking for shade ♪

15:10.105 --> 15:13.896
♪ I lick shots at the brutal charade
As the polls close like a casket ♪

15:13.980 --> 15:17.146
♪ On truth devoured
Silent play on the shadow of power ♪

15:17.230 --> 15:19.313
♪ A spectacle, monopolized ♪

15:19.396 --> 15:21.730
♪ The camera's eyes on choice disguised ♪

15:21.813 --> 15:23.855
♪ Was it cast for the mass
Who burn and toil? ♪

15:23.938 --> 15:25.938
♪ Or for the vultures
Who thirst for blood and oil? ♪

15:26.021 --> 15:28.771
♪ Yes, a spectacle, monopolized ♪

15:28.855 --> 15:30.771
♪ They hold the reins, stole your eyes ♪

15:30.855 --> 15:33.188
♪ All the Fistagons
The bullets and bombs ♪

15:33.271 --> 15:35.896
♪ Who stuff the banks
Who staff the party ranks ♪

15:35.980 --> 15:38.021
♪ More for Gore
Or the son of a drug lord ♪

15:38.105 --> 15:40.521
♪ None of the above
Fuck it, cut the cord ♪

15:40.605 --> 15:43.355
♪ Lights out, guerrilla radio ♪

15:43.438 --> 15:44.813
♪ Turn that shit up ♪

15:44.896 --> 15:47.855
♪ Lights out, guerrilla radio ♪

15:48.438 --> 15:49.646
♪ Turn that shit up ♪

15:49.730 --> 15:52.313
♪ Lights out, guerrilla radio ♪

15:53.396 --> 15:54.855
-♪ Turn that shit-- ♪
-[song halts]

15:59.230 --> 16:00.230
[panting]

16:01.646 --> 16:02.646
Huh?

16:03.646 --> 16:05.396
How the fuck?

16:06.605 --> 16:07.938
Ah, don't feel bad.

16:08.021 --> 16:09.605
I heal extremely fast.

16:09.688 --> 16:11.188
Like a superhero.

16:11.271 --> 16:13.730
Not that I call myself a superhero,

16:13.813 --> 16:14.730
but your mom does.

16:14.813 --> 16:16.021
[panicked grunting]

16:18.313 --> 16:19.146
[Ken] Shoryuken!

16:19.980 --> 16:21.063
[announcer] You win!

16:21.563 --> 16:22.438
Perfect.

16:24.855 --> 16:25.855
[guns cocking]

16:28.980 --> 16:29.980
[rapid gunfire]

16:32.021 --> 16:33.896
[gunfire continuing faintly]

16:37.230 --> 16:38.146
[agent] Hey, Pat.

16:38.230 --> 16:40.355
Our boys still getting their asses kicked?

16:41.646 --> 16:42.480
Yep.

16:43.813 --> 16:45.771
I feel bad for you, Doc.

16:45.855 --> 16:48.730
First time in the field,
and we're not even going to see action.

16:48.813 --> 16:53.063
Mm-mm. My brain is too valuable
to risk taking into a combat zone.

16:53.146 --> 16:55.355
I only came so I can examine
the quantum transmitter

16:55.438 --> 16:57.021
at the soonest possible moment.

16:57.105 --> 17:00.480
Come on, you don't want to pick up
a sweet battle scar like my man here?

17:00.563 --> 17:01.396
King.

17:01.480 --> 17:03.480
What? I'm saying he's a badass.

17:03.563 --> 17:05.938
You went toe-to-paw
with the White Rabbit and lived.

17:06.021 --> 17:07.771
I got lucky, that's all.

17:07.855 --> 17:09.063
[Pat] Whoa, whoa, whoa.

17:09.146 --> 17:11.563
Yo, yo, yo, yo. What was that?

17:11.646 --> 17:13.563
[Dante speaking inaudibly]

17:13.646 --> 17:15.271
[Pat] It looks like he can heal himself.

17:15.355 --> 17:17.355
Any explanations there, Doc?

17:17.438 --> 17:20.021
Uh, not at the moment.

17:20.105 --> 17:22.105
Is he genetically enhanced somehow?

17:22.188 --> 17:24.021
[Mary over radio] I have a theory.

17:26.521 --> 17:28.271
I'll be testing it shortly.

17:28.896 --> 17:32.188
Great, so the guy's
some sort of super soldier,

17:32.271 --> 17:33.813
and he's wearing half the transmitter

17:33.896 --> 17:37.855
that keeps our reality
from being swarmed by the armies of Hell

17:37.938 --> 17:39.438
as a necklace.

17:39.521 --> 17:42.771
Yeah, he really is
just wearing it, isn't he?

17:43.271 --> 17:45.605
Kind of makes you question
Sparda's whole plan.

17:45.688 --> 17:50.438
Excuse me, but, um, what's an ancient
Greek city-state got to do with this?

17:50.521 --> 17:53.480
Not Sparta, Sparda.

17:53.563 --> 17:57.271
Did no one read
the intelligence briefing I prepared?

17:58.188 --> 17:59.188
[Mary] I read it.

18:00.105 --> 18:01.105
Thank you.

18:03.271 --> 18:07.813
Sparda's the one Hell dweller who
might be worth not vaporizing on sight.

18:07.896 --> 18:11.646
He was a demon knight,
whatever that means.

18:11.730 --> 18:15.396
Big bad warrior, blah blah blah.

18:15.480 --> 18:18.980
Served as the right hand of Mundus,
the demons' king,

18:19.063 --> 18:23.313
2,000 years ago when our world
was still connected to their shithole.

18:23.396 --> 18:27.146
And Mundus wasn't happy
just ruling the shithole.

18:27.230 --> 18:29.313
He wanted to conquer humanity,

18:29.396 --> 18:31.521
make slaves of us all.

18:31.605 --> 18:33.021
Typical demon shit.

18:33.521 --> 18:36.188
And I guess Sparda woke up
one day and realized,

18:36.688 --> 18:39.771
"Hey, this is evil as fuck,"

18:39.855 --> 18:41.230
so he rebelled.

18:41.313 --> 18:45.980
He fought against Mundus, taking out
hundreds of his own former legions.

18:46.063 --> 18:48.188
Kind of the least
he could fucking do, really.

18:49.688 --> 18:52.938
But even he couldn't stop
an entire world of abominations.

18:53.980 --> 18:58.188
The only way to protect humanity was
to seal the realms off from each other.

18:59.646 --> 19:02.271
He himself stayed on our side.

19:03.105 --> 19:05.063
Which, if that's true,

19:05.146 --> 19:07.021
he's been MI-fucking-A

19:07.105 --> 19:09.605
whenever shit hits the fan
for the past few millennia.

19:14.396 --> 19:17.646
So, maybe he is
just another pit-beast after all.

19:18.146 --> 19:19.646
[aggressive metal music playing]

19:32.146 --> 19:33.313
[music subsides]

19:34.146 --> 19:36.605
Dante, remember me?

19:36.688 --> 19:37.813
Let's see.

19:37.896 --> 19:39.605
Seven feet tall,

19:39.688 --> 19:42.355
face like someone carved
a gargoyle out of beef jerky?

19:42.855 --> 19:43.771
I do remember.

19:43.855 --> 19:45.563
Arnie, right? How are the kids?

19:45.646 --> 19:47.646
Great, thanks.

19:47.730 --> 19:49.355
Julie just got into Yale.

19:49.438 --> 19:51.438
[chuckles] So, look.

19:51.521 --> 19:55.605
Uh, there's a big-ass bounty
on that necklace of yours.

19:55.688 --> 19:56.896
I was thinking,

19:56.980 --> 19:59.480
you and me bring it in together, huh?

19:59.563 --> 20:01.063
Split the dough.

20:01.855 --> 20:03.146
Fifty-fifty.

20:03.230 --> 20:05.980
[raising voice]
That's a better offer than someone made.

20:06.605 --> 20:07.980
[groaning]

20:08.063 --> 20:09.813
But it's gonna be a hard no.

20:09.896 --> 20:11.605
Ah, worth a shot.

20:12.438 --> 20:14.105
Sorry about the place.

20:14.188 --> 20:15.396
No hard feelings?

20:16.855 --> 20:18.855
[aggressive metal music building]

20:30.938 --> 20:31.938
[music subsides]

20:38.646 --> 20:43.730
Aw, I thought the big guy would get
at least a hit in or something. Man!

20:43.813 --> 20:46.771
These dudes give
low-life hired killers a bad name.

20:50.855 --> 20:51.980
[agent] Oh.

20:52.063 --> 20:53.146
Your daughters?

20:53.646 --> 20:55.230
I'm all they've got, you know?

20:55.313 --> 20:57.730
I went to sign up for the army.
No other option.

20:57.813 --> 21:01.521
This recruiter comes to me saying,
"Join the important fight from home."

21:01.605 --> 21:03.730
He left out
the demons from Hell part, though.

21:03.813 --> 21:05.938
Kinda wish he'd led with
"the demons from Hell" part.

21:06.021 --> 21:07.396
Might've answered differently.

21:09.021 --> 21:09.938
[Mary] It's time.

21:10.980 --> 21:11.896
I'm going in.

21:11.980 --> 21:13.230
Copy that, Lieutenant.

21:13.313 --> 21:15.063
You sure you don't need any help?

21:15.146 --> 21:16.771
Just get the truck warmed up.

21:16.855 --> 21:18.896
[industrial music pulsing]

21:51.521 --> 21:52.521
[Dante grunts]

21:53.230 --> 21:56.105
Hey. That was actually kinda close.

21:56.188 --> 21:58.188
Closer than you think.

22:10.188 --> 22:11.230
Hey!

22:12.646 --> 22:14.146
[Dante coughing]

22:21.896 --> 22:24.355
Of course the goon squad was a misdirect.

22:25.563 --> 22:27.063
Who was that chick?

22:27.146 --> 22:29.688
[growls suggestively] What a woman!

22:29.771 --> 22:31.480
I don't care who she is.

22:32.355 --> 22:33.521
I made a promise.

22:34.688 --> 22:36.271
And I'm going to keep it.

22:37.021 --> 22:38.813
[Enzo murmurs mockingly]

22:39.938 --> 22:42.813
So, who here's looking for representation?

22:44.230 --> 22:45.730
[frenetic industrial music pulsing]

22:56.938 --> 22:57.771
Hey, lady.

23:17.271 --> 23:19.521
Ow. What's in that thing?

23:19.605 --> 23:21.688
I watched you fighting and wondered,

23:21.771 --> 23:25.146
"What the fuck kind of person
could shake off bullets like that?"

23:25.230 --> 23:27.355
A really, really awesome one.

23:27.438 --> 23:29.230
Or not a person at all.

23:29.313 --> 23:31.646
That was an anti-demon round
I hit you with.

23:31.730 --> 23:36.688
Which means, no matter how good
you might be at hiding it, you're a demon.

23:40.230 --> 23:41.313
[gasps]

23:42.396 --> 23:44.605
Ripped and irresistible dreamboat, I know.

23:44.688 --> 23:46.396
Still can't just tear a guy's clothes off.

23:46.480 --> 23:47.646
You're not demon.

23:47.730 --> 23:48.855
But your blood…

23:49.355 --> 23:50.980
I've heard it was possible.

23:51.063 --> 23:53.105
I never thought I'd see one, though.

23:53.188 --> 23:54.146
You're a hybrid.

23:54.230 --> 23:56.438
Part human. Part demon.

23:56.521 --> 23:58.396
Wait. You think I'm part demon?

23:58.480 --> 24:01.021
You are.
And I've got the one weapon on Earth--

24:26.188 --> 24:28.855
[Mary grunts, yells]

24:40.896 --> 24:42.438
Seriously? Part demon?

24:42.521 --> 24:46.271
If you knew how many of those I've killed,
you'd know how crazy you sound.

24:46.355 --> 24:48.896
Demons kill their own all the time.

24:48.980 --> 24:51.730
Death and destruction
is the core of your nature.

24:51.813 --> 24:54.021
Trust me, I know all about demons' nature.

24:54.105 --> 24:55.105
I'm not one of them.

24:55.188 --> 24:58.438
How else can you explain
what you're capable of?

24:58.521 --> 25:00.021
You even fight like they do.

25:00.105 --> 25:02.688
Unholy strength but no intelligence.

25:02.771 --> 25:03.855
No strategy.

25:03.938 --> 25:06.730
I don't know.
Seems like I managed to catch you.

25:06.813 --> 25:08.688
And since we're getting so personal,

25:09.771 --> 25:12.563
what does everyone want
with my mom's necklace?

25:12.646 --> 25:15.396
You don't even know
what this really is, do you?

25:16.396 --> 25:17.813
I know that it's mine!

25:17.896 --> 25:19.480
All yours, Hellblood.

25:27.480 --> 25:29.021
[music intensifies]

25:39.063 --> 25:40.438
[music subsides]

25:48.688 --> 25:49.688
[door creaks]

25:54.230 --> 25:55.188
Jackpot!

25:56.188 --> 25:57.021
Oh.

26:03.146 --> 26:04.146
[Dante grunting]

26:07.605 --> 26:11.063
Usually we don't bother
taking members of your species prisoner.

26:11.730 --> 26:13.396
But we do have the tech for it.

26:13.480 --> 26:15.355
To cover special circumstances.

26:21.021 --> 26:24.605
Insurance. Just in case
you manage to get out of the truck.

26:25.271 --> 26:26.188
What truck?

26:42.980 --> 26:45.146
Who caught who now, motherfucker?

26:49.771 --> 26:50.771
["Devils Never Cry" plays]

26:50.855 --> 26:52.230
♪ Bless me ♪

26:52.313 --> 26:58.313
♪ With the leaf off of the tree ♪

26:58.396 --> 27:02.230
♪ On it, I see ♪

27:02.313 --> 27:06.188
♪ The freedom reign ♪

27:06.271 --> 27:10.063
♪ We are falling ♪

27:10.146 --> 27:13.896
♪ The light is calling ♪

27:13.980 --> 27:17.813
♪ Tears inside me ♪

27:17.896 --> 27:21.771
♪ Calm me down ♪

27:21.855 --> 27:25.563
♪ Midnight calling ♪

27:25.646 --> 27:29.480
♪ Mist of resolving ♪

27:29.563 --> 27:31.521
♪ Crown me ♪

27:31.605 --> 27:37.355
♪ With the pure, green leaf ♪

27:37.438 --> 27:41.230
♪ Praise to my father ♪

27:41.313 --> 27:45.146
♪ Blessed by the water ♪

27:45.230 --> 27:49.146
♪ Black light, dark sky ♪

27:49.230 --> 27:51.021
IN MEMORY OF KEVIN CONROY (1955-2022)

27:51.105 --> 27:53.980
♪ The devil's cry ♪